[These articles were published one day apart, but they differ in their reporting numbers. It is likely that there are 6 confirmed cases, as it is possible that a positive report was received late on 24 Nov 2016, to be reported on 25 Nov 2016.

It is good news that feed lots are being allowed and fellow ranchers and the government are likely to assist them. Keeping calves through the winter requires quite a lot of extra feed that is probably not budgeted for by anyone.

We wish the producers good luck as well as those involved in the tracing of this disease. - Mod.TG

